investigation.title: Age and Space Irradiation Modulate Tumor Progression: Implications for Carcinogenesis Risk
investigation.description: Age plays a major role in tumor incidence and is an important consideration when modeling the carcinogenesis process or estimating cancer risks. Epidemiological data show that from adolescence through middle age, cancer incidence increases with age.
